race.description: Tab Regional Championship Final Mobile Pace
race.comment: ALWAYS BE CHAPS (5) made it two wins from the past three outings when he led from this same draw to score by just over a metre at his latest appearance. That took his strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent and all 11 career wins have come here. Could do it again. WALTER WARLOCK (6) missed by just a nose as favourite in his heat, leading from a similar draw and fighting on well. That was his first outing for nearly four weeks since the Breeders Challenge series where he won a heat here and placed in a Menangle semi-final. Fitter so is a big chance to go one better. GROSSO NASO (1) led from a few spots wider to place here last start. Should be close to peak fitness third-up and has the pace to be prominent from the inside draw. Last-start winner ROUGE BLING (3) has been very consistent and draws to be competitive again.
